<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8943] Split Thrift2&apos;s ThriftServer into separate classes for easier testing and modularization</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8943</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the ThriftServer class in Thrift 2 sets up and starts the actual server. Better follow a similar pattern to Thrift 1 where there is some factory setting up the server, and a separate start section. That way it is easier to test if the setup of the server is picking up everything it needs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
